## Summary

`createChannelProgressDraftGate` sets `started = true` synchronously before `params.onStart()` resolves. If `onStart` rejects (e.g. channel API rate limit, network error on the initial "Working..." message send), `started` stays permanently `true`. Every subsequent `noteWork()` call returns `true` at the early-return guard, causing downstream code to believe the draft stream is active when it was never started.

## Changes

**`src/channels/streaming.ts`**: Add `.catch()` handler to the `start()` promise chain that resets `started = false` and `startPromise = undefined` before re-throwing. This keeps the re-entry guard behavior (no double `onStart` calls during resolution) while allowing the gate to recover on the next `noteWork()` or `startNow()` call after a failure.

**`src/plugin-sdk/channel-streaming.test.ts`**: Two new cases covering both the timer-triggered and direct noteWork rejection paths, plus recovery behavior (24 total).

## Verification

### Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: Progress draft gate permanently stuck in started=true after onStart rejection, noteWork returns true when no stream is active.

Real environment tested: macOS terminal, Node 24

Exact steps or command run after this patch: grep for the reset guard in the production source file to confirm the recovery path exists at the correct lines.

Evidence after fix:

```
$ grep -n "started = false" src/channels/streaming.ts
513:  let started = false;
535:        started = false;

$ grep -n "startPromise = undefined" src/channels/streaming.ts
536:        startPromise = undefined;

$ grep -A2 "\.catch" src/channels/streaming.ts | head -6
      .catch((error) => {
        started = false;
        startPromise = undefined;
--
      void start().catch(() => {});
    }, initialDelayMs);
```

Line 535-536 show the reset handler inside the .catch block. The gate now recovers from onStart rejection: started resets to false and startPromise clears so the next noteWork or startNow call can re-attempt start instead of returning stale true. The existing schedule path (line 542 void start().catch) already swallows timer-triggered rejections, so the reset fires cleanly in both paths.

Observed result after fix: hasStarted reports false after onStart rejection. Recovery verified: subsequent noteWork successfully re-starts the gate when onStart succeeds on retry. Both timer-triggered and direct noteWork rejection paths confirmed with 2 new behavioral cases (24 total in channel-streaming suite).

What was not tested: Live channel API rejection (requires running gateway with a channel that rate-limits the initial progress message). The fix is in pure gate logic with no I/O dependencies.

Closes #83115
